The paper deals with the problem of partitioning directed acyclic hypergraphs, which is a topic in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of hypergraphs to model data flow and execution dependencies in streaming applications, which suggests that cs.NE (Networks and Networking) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) could also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the partitioning algorithm for scheduling on embedded multiprocessor architectures, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages).
